[2026-03-18T18:35:07.035Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TTNuZaKLtbV566JuRfX3m3","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have gathered comprehensive information about the audit system. Let me compile the full report with all the relevant findings.\n\n## Comprehensive Audit System Analysis\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's the complete breakdown of the audit system:\n\n---\n\n### 1. THE AUDITLOG CLASS (auditLog.ts)\n\n**File:** `C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\auditLog.ts`\n\n#### Key Components:\n\n**Statement Cache:**\n- Private member: `queryStmtCache = new Map<string, Database.Statement>()`\n- Located at line 286\n- Caches prepared SQL statements to avoid recompilation\n\n**query() Method (lines 446-476):**\n```typescript\nquery(opts?: {\n  tenantId?: string;\n  action?: AuditAction;\n  since?: string;\n  limit?: number;\n  offset?: number;\n}): AuditEvent[]\n```\n\n**How SQL Queries Are Built:**\n1. **Dynamic WHERE clause construction** (lines 454-460):\n   - Builds `clauses` array with filter conditions\n   - Builds `keyParts` array to create cache key\n   - Parameters are added to `params` array\n   \n2. **Cache Key Generation** (line 462):\n   ```typescript\n   const key = keyParts.join('-') || 'none';\n   ```\n   - Possible keys: `'none'`, `'tenant'`, `'action'`, `'since'`, `'tenant-action'`, `'tenant-since'`, `'action-since'`, `'tenant-action-since'`\n\n3. **Statement Cache Lookup** (lines 463-469):\n   ```typescript\n   let stmt = this.queryStmtCache.get(key);\n   if (!stmt) {\n     const where = clauses.length > 0 ? `WHERE ${clauses.join(' AND ')}` : '';\n     stmt = this.db.prepare(\n       `SELECT * FROM audit_events ${where} ORDER BY id DESC LIMIT ? OFFSET ?`,\n     );\n     this.queryStmtCache.set(key, stmt);\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Query Execution** (line 475):\n   ```typescript\n   return stmt.all(...params, limit, offset) as AuditEvent[];\n   ```\n   - Uses prepared statement with all parameters passed as bindings (safe from SQL injection)\n\n#### Database Schema (AUDIT_SCHEMA, lines 26-43):\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS audit_events (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n  timestamp TEXT NOT NULL,\n  action TEXT NOT NULL,\n  tenant_id TEXT,\n  actor TEXT,\n  resource_type TEXT,\n  resource_id TEXT,\n  detail TEXT,\n  ip_address TEXT,\n  prev_hash TEXT\n);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_audit_ts ON audit_events(timestamp);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_audit_tenant_action_ts ON audit_events(tenant_id, action, timestamp);\nDROP INDEX IF EXISTS idx_audit_tenant_ts;\nDROP INDEX IF EXISTS idx_audit_action;\n```\n\n#### Indexes:\n- `idx_audit_ts` on `timestamp` (for temporal queries)\n- `idx_audit_tenant_action_ts` on `(tenant_id, action, timestamp)` (composite index for filtered queries)\n\n#### Hash Chain Verification:\n- **Chain Hash Computation** (lines 12-24): SHA-256 hash chain for tamper detection\n- **verify() Method** (lines 489-543): Validates hash chain integrity across all entries\n- `prev_hash` column stores the SHA-256 chain hash for each entry\n\n#### Other Methods:\n- `record(entry)`: Append to in-memory buffer (line 364)\n- `flush()`: Flush buffered entries with transaction (line 381)\n- `countEvents()`: Count total entries (line 336)\n- `purgeOlderThan()`: Delete old entries in chunks (line 349)\n- `stats()`: Return aggregated statistics (line 403)\n\n#### Buffering Strategy:\n- Buffer flush size: 50 entries (BUFFER_FLUSH_SIZE, line 268)\n- Flush interval: 100ms (BUFFER_FLUSH_INTERVAL_MS, line 270)\n- Batch inserts wrapped in single transaction for atomic writes\n\n---\n\n### 2. HTTP ENDPOINT: GET /api/admin/audit\n\n**File:** `C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\httpApi.ts`\n\n**Handler Location:** Lines 203-216\n\n```typescript\nexactRoutes.set('GET:/api/admin/audit', {\n  adminOnly: true,\n  handler: (_req, res, _ctx, _route, queryString) => {\n    if (!auditLog) { json(res, 200, []); return; }\n    const params = new URLSearchParams(queryString || '');\n    json(res, 200, auditLog.query({\n      tenantId: params.get('tenantId') ?? undefined,\n      action: (params.get('action') ?? undefined) as AuditAction | undefined,\n      since: params.get('since') ?? undefined,\n      limit: clampQueryInt(params.get('limit'), 100, MAX_QUERY_LIMIT),\n      offset: clampQueryInt(params.get('offset'), 0, MAX_QUERY_OFFSET),\n    }));\n  },\n});\n```\n\n**Query Parameters:**\n- `tenantId` (string): Filter by tenant\n- `action` (AuditAction): Filter by action type\n- `since` (string): ISO timestamp for temporal filtering\n- `limit` (integer): Max results, clamped to [0, 500] with default 100\n- `offset` (integer): Pagination offset, clamped to [0, 100000] with default 0\n\n**Related Endpoint:** GET /api/admin/audit/stats (lines 218-231)\n\n```typescript\nexactRoutes.set('GET:/api/admin/audit/stats', {\n  adminOnly: true,\n  handler: (_req, res, _ctx, _route, queryString) => {\n    if (!auditLog) { json(res, 200, { byAction: [], byTenant: [], topActors: [], trend: [] }); return; }\n    const params = new URLSearchParams(queryString || '');\n    const bucket = params.get('bucket') === 'hour' ? 'hour' : 'day';\n    json(res, 200, auditLog.stats({\n      tenantId: params.get('tenantId') ?? undefined,\n      since: params.get('since') ?? undefined,\n      until: params.get('until') ?? undefined,\n      bucket,\n    }));\n  },\n});\n```\n\n**Verify Endpoint:** POST /api/admin/audit/verify (lines 233-247)\n- Verifies hash chain integrity with optional time range filters\n\n---\n\n### 3. TYPE DEFINITIONS\n\n**File:** `C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\auditLog.ts`\n\n#### AuditEvent Interface (lines 246-258):\n```typescript\nexport interface AuditEvent {\n  id: number;\n  timestamp: string;\n  action: string;\n  tenant_id: string | null;\n  actor: string | null;\n  resource_type: string | null;\n  resource_id: string | null;\n  detail: string | null;\n  ip_address: string | null;\n  prev_hash: string | null;\n}\n```\n\n#### AuditEntry (Discriminated Union, lines 217-241):\nAll audit entry types including:\n- `KeyEncryptEntry`, `KeyDecryptEntry`, `KeyDecryptFailedEntry`, `KeyDeleteEntry`, `KeyAccessEntry`, `KeyDeriveEntry`\n- `PersonaCreateEntry`, `PersonaDeleteEntry`\n- `ToolLinkEntry`, `ToolDefinitionCreateEntry`\n- `CredentialLinkEntry`\n- `SubscriptionCreateEntry`, `SubscriptionUpdateEntry`, `SubscriptionDeleteEntry`\n- `WorkerConnectedEntry`, `WorkerDisconnectedEntry`\n- `TriggerCreateEntry`, `TriggerUpdateEntry`, `TriggerDeleteEntry`\n- `EventPublishEntry`, `EventUpdateEntry`\n- `ExecutionSubmitEntry`\n- `WebhookReceiveEntry`\n\n#### AuditAction Type (line 244):\n```typescript\nexport type AuditAction = AuditEntry['action'];\n```\nString literal union of all valid audit action names.\n\n#### ChainVerifyResult (lines 260-265):\n```typescript\nexport interface ChainVerifyResult {\n  valid: boolean;\n  verifiedCount: number;\n  brokenAtId?: number;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. INITIALIZATION & LIFECYCLE\n\n**File:** `C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\index.ts` (lines 64-66)\n\n```typescript\nconst auditLog = new AuditLog(config.auditDbPath, logger);\nconst auditRetention = new AuditRetentionPolicy(auditLog, config.auditRetentionDays, logger);\nauditRetention.startDailyPurge();\n```\n\n**Constructor** (lines 292-328):\n- Creates separate SQLite database at `dbPath`\n- Enables WAL mode for concurrency\n- Applies schema and migrations\n- Initializes chain from last stored hash\n- Sets up batch insert transaction wrapper\n- Starts 100ms flush timer\n\n---\n\n### 5. AUDIT RETENTION POLICY\n\n**File:** `C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\auditRetentionPolicy.ts`\n\n- Minimum retention: 90 days (can be configured via `auditRetentionDays` in config)\n- Enforces append-only semantics (separate class handles deletions)\n- Daily purge job runs asynchronously\n- Purges in chunks to prevent event loop starvation\n- Deleted entries may break hash chain (by design - detectable)\n\n---\n\n### 6. KEY SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS\n\n1. **SQL Injection Protection**: Uses parameterized queries with prepared statement bindings\n2. **Hash Chain**: SHA-256 chain commits entire history to each entry\n3. **Append-Only**: Buffering and transaction structure ensures atomicity\n4. **Admin-Only Access**: Both `/api/admin/audit` and `/api/admin/audit/verify` require admin authentication\n5. **Statement Cache**: Limits recompilation, 8 possible cache keys maximum\n6. **Tamper Detection**: `verify()` method detects chain breaks from deletion or mutation\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Files:\n\n1. **C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\auditLog.ts** - Core audit log implementation with query method, hash chain, and buffering\n2. **C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\httpApi.ts** - HTTP endpoints (lines 203-247) handling audit queries\n3. **C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\db\\schema.ts** - Schema definitions (system-level, not audit-specific)\n4. **C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\auditPolicy.ts** - Event-to-audit mapping declarative policy\n5. **C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\auditRetentionPolicy.ts** - Retention lifecycle management\n6. **C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\index.ts** - Initialization and wiring"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a35142e52d988596d (use SendMessage with to: 'a35142e52d988596d' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 54995\ntool_uses: 13\nduration_ms: 43405</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2f4f2ce6-4bd2-4ba0-af5f-a82e0e15723d","uuid":"59a2c73b-69b2-43fe-b425-f76ea97ce27d","timestamp":"2026-03-18T18:35:06.955Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the audit system in this codebase thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The AuditLog class - its query() method, how it builds SQL queries, the statement cache\n2. The GET /api/admin/audit HTTP endpoint - how it parses query params and calls AuditLog.query()\n3. The database schema for the audit_log table (look for CREATE TABLE statements)\n4. The types used (AuditEntry, query filter types, etc.)\n5. Any existing indexes on the audit_log table\n\nLook in:\n- packages/orchestrator/src/auditLog.ts\n- packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts or similar HTTP handler files\n- packages/orchestrator/src/db/ directory\n- packages/shared/src/types.ts\n\nProvide the full content of the most relevant files, especially auditLog.ts and any HTTP handler that serves the audit endpoint.","agentId":"a35142e52d988596d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have gathered comprehensive information about the audit system. Let me compile the full report with all the relevant findings.\n\n## Comprehensive Audit System Analysis\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's the complete breakdown of the audit system:\n\n---\n\n### 1. THE AUDITLOG CLASS (auditLog.ts)\n\n**File:** `C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\auditLog.ts`\n\n#### Key Components:\n\n**Statement Cache:**\n- Private member: `queryStmtCache = new Map<string, Database.Statement>()`\n- Located at line 286\n- Caches prepared SQL statements to avoid recompilation\n\n**query() Method (lines 446-476):**\n```typescript\nquery(opts?: {\n  tenantId?: string;\n  action?: AuditAction;\n  since?: string;\n  limit?: number;\n  offset?: number;\n}): AuditEvent[]\n```\n\n**How SQL Queries Are Built:**\n1. **Dynamic WHERE clause construction** (lines 454-460):\n   - Builds `clauses` array with filter conditions\n   - Builds `keyParts` array to create cache key\n   - Parameters are added to `params` array\n   \n2. **Cache Key Generation** (line 462):\n   ```typescript\n   const key = keyParts.join('-') || 'none';\n   ```\n   - Possible keys: `'none'`, `'tenant'`, `'action'`, `'since'`, `'tenant-action'`, `'tenant-since'`, `'action-since'`, `'tenant-action-since'`\n\n3. **Statement Cache Lookup** (lines 463-469):\n   ```typescript\n   let stmt = this.queryStmtCache.get(key);\n   if (!stmt) {\n     const where = clauses.length > 0 ? `WHERE ${clauses.join(' AND ')}` : '';\n     stmt = this.db.prepare(\n       `SELECT * FROM audit_events ${where} ORDER BY id DESC LIMIT ? OFFSET ?`,\n     );\n     this.queryStmtCache.set(key, stmt);\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Query Execution** (line 475):\n   ```typescript\n   return stmt.all(...params, limit, offset) as AuditEvent[];\n   ```\n   - Uses prepared statement with all parameters passed as bindings (safe from SQL injection)\n\n#### Database Schema (AUDIT_SCHEMA, lines 26-43):\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS audit_events (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n  timestamp TEXT NOT NULL,\n  action TEXT NOT NULL,\n  tenant_id TEXT,\n  actor TEXT,\n  resource_type TEXT,\n  resource_id TEXT,\n  detail TEXT,\n  ip_address TEXT,\n  prev_hash TEXT\n);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_audit_ts ON audit_events(timestamp);\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_audit_tenant_action_ts ON audit_events(tenant_id, action, timestamp);\nDROP INDEX IF EXISTS idx_audit_tenant_ts;\nDROP INDEX IF EXISTS idx_audit_action;\n```\n\n#### Indexes:\n- `idx_audit_ts` on `timestamp` (for temporal queries)\n- `idx_audit_tenant_action_ts` on `(tenant_id, action, timestamp)` (composite index for filtered queries)\n\n#### Hash Chain Verification:\n- **Chain Hash Computation** (lines 12-24): SHA-256 hash chain for tamper detection\n- **verify() Method** (lines 489-543): Validates hash chain integrity across all entries\n- `prev_hash` column stores the SHA-256 chain hash for each entry\n\n#### Other Methods:\n- `record(entry)`: Append to in-memory buffer (line 364)\n- `flush()`: Flush buffered entries with transaction (line 381)\n- `countEvents()`: Count total entries (line 336)\n- `purgeOlderThan()`: Delete old entries in chunks (line 349)\n- `stats()`: Return aggregated statistics (line 403)\n\n#### Buffering Strategy:\n- Buffer flush size: 50 entries (BUFFER_FLUSH_SIZE, line 268)\n- Flush interval: 100ms (BUFFER_FLUSH_INTERVAL_MS, line 270)\n- Batch inserts wrapped in single transaction for atomic writes\n\n---\n\n### 2. HTTP ENDPOINT: GET /api/admin/audit\n\n**File:** `C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\httpApi.ts`\n\n**Handler Location:** Lines 203-216\n\n```typescript\nexactRoutes.set('GET:/api/admin/audit', {\n  adminOnly: true,\n  handler: (_req, res, _ctx, _route, queryString) => {\n    if (!auditLog) { json(res, 200, []); return; }\n    const params = new URLSearchParams(queryString || '');\n    json(res, 200, auditLog.query({\n      tenantId: params.get('tenantId') ?? undefined,\n      action: (params.get('action') ?? undefined) as AuditAction | undefined,\n      since: params.get('since') ?? undefined,\n      limit: clampQueryInt(params.get('limit'), 100, MAX_QUERY_LIMIT),\n      offset: clampQueryInt(params.get('offset'), 0, MAX_QUERY_OFFSET),\n    }));\n  },\n});\n```\n\n**Query Parameters:**\n- `tenantId` (string): Filter by tenant\n- `action` (AuditAction): Filter by action type\n- `since` (string): ISO timestamp for temporal filtering\n- `limit` (integer): Max results, clamped to [0, 500] with default 100\n- `offset` (integer): Pagination offset, clamped to [0, 100000] with default 0\n\n**Related Endpoint:** GET /api/admin/audit/stats (lines 218-231)\n\n```typescript\nexactRoutes.set('GET:/api/admin/audit/stats', {\n  adminOnly: true,\n  handler: (_req, res, _ctx, _route, queryString) => {\n    if (!auditLog) { json(res, 200, { byAction: [], byTenant: [], topActors: [], trend: [] }); return; }\n    const params = new URLSearchParams(queryString || '');\n    const bucket = params.get('bucket') === 'hour' ? 'hour' : 'day';\n    json(res, 200, auditLog.stats({\n      tenantId: params.get('tenantId') ?? undefined,\n      since: params.get('since') ?? undefined,\n      until: params.get('until') ?? undefined,\n      bucket,\n    }));\n  },\n});\n```\n\n**Verify Endpoint:** POST /api/admin/audit/verify (lines 233-247)\n- Verifies hash chain integrity with optional time range filters\n\n---\n\n### 3. TYPE DEFINITIONS\n\n**File:** `C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\auditLog.ts`\n\n#### AuditEvent Interface (lines 246-258):\n```typescript\nexport interface AuditEvent {\n  id: number;\n  timestamp: string;\n  action: string;\n  tenant_id: string | null;\n  actor: string | null;\n  resource_type: string | null;\n  resource_id: string | null;\n  detail: string | null;\n  ip_address: string | null;\n  prev_hash: string | null;\n}\n```\n\n#### AuditEntry (Discriminated Union, lines 217-241):\nAll audit entry types including:\n- `KeyEncryptEntry`, `KeyDecryptEntry`, `KeyDecryptFailedEntry`, `KeyDeleteEntry`, `KeyAccessEntry`, `KeyDeriveEntry`\n- `PersonaCreateEntry`, `PersonaDeleteEntry`\n- `ToolLinkEntry`, `ToolDefinitionCreateEntry`\n- `CredentialLinkEntry`\n- `SubscriptionCreateEntry`, `SubscriptionUpdateEntry`, `SubscriptionDeleteEntry`\n- `WorkerConnectedEntry`, `WorkerDisconnectedEntry`\n- `TriggerCreateEntry`, `TriggerUpdateEntry`, `TriggerDeleteEntry`\n- `EventPublishEntry`, `EventUpdateEntry`\n- `ExecutionSubmitEntry`\n- `WebhookReceiveEntry`\n\n#### AuditAction Type (line 244):\n```typescript\nexport type AuditAction = AuditEntry['action'];\n```\nString literal union of all valid audit action names.\n\n#### ChainVerifyResult (lines 260-265):\n```typescript\nexport interface ChainVerifyResult {\n  valid: boolean;\n  verifiedCount: number;\n  brokenAtId?: number;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. INITIALIZATION & LIFECYCLE\n\n**File:** `C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\index.ts` (lines 64-66)\n\n```typescript\nconst auditLog = new AuditLog(config.auditDbPath, logger);\nconst auditRetention = new AuditRetentionPolicy(auditLog, config.auditRetentionDays, logger);\nauditRetention.startDailyPurge();\n```\n\n**Constructor** (lines 292-328):\n- Creates separate SQLite database at `dbPath`\n- Enables WAL mode for concurrency\n- Applies schema and migrations\n- Initializes chain from last stored hash\n- Sets up batch insert transaction wrapper\n- Starts 100ms flush timer\n\n---\n\n### 5. AUDIT RETENTION POLICY\n\n**File:** `C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\auditRetentionPolicy.ts`\n\n- Minimum retention: 90 days (can be configured via `auditRetentionDays` in config)\n- Enforces append-only semantics (separate class handles deletions)\n- Daily purge job runs asynchronously\n- Purges in chunks to prevent event loop starvation\n- Deleted entries may break hash chain (by design - detectable)\n\n---\n\n### 6. KEY SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS\n\n1. **SQL Injection Protection**: Uses parameterized queries with prepared statement bindings\n2. **Hash Chain**: SHA-256 chain commits entire history to each entry\n3. **Append-Only**: Buffering and transaction structure ensures atomicity\n4. **Admin-Only Access**: Both `/api/admin/audit` and `/api/admin/audit/verify` require admin authentication\n5. **Statement Cache**: Limits recompilation, 8 possible cache keys maximum\n6. **Tamper Detection**: `verify()` method detects chain breaks from deletion or mutation\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Files:\n\n1. **C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\auditLog.ts** - Core audit log implementation with query method, hash chain, and buffering\n2. **C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\httpApi.ts** - HTTP endpoints (lines 203-247) handling audit queries\n3. **C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\orchestrator\\src\\db\\schema.ts** - Schema definitions (system-level, not audit-specific)\n4.